SimpleType.name: Modelica.Fluid.Types.ModelStructure
SimpleType.description: Enumeration with choices for model structure in distributed pipe model

Item.name: av_vb
Item.description: av_vb: port_a - volume - flow model - volume - port_b

Item.name: a_v_b
Item.description: a_v_b: port_a - flow model - volume - flow model - port_b

Item.name: av_b
Item.description: av_b: port_a - volume - flow model - port_b

Item.name: a_vb
Item.description: a_vb: port_a - flow model - volume - port_b

Item.name: never
Item.description: Do not use as state at all.

Item.name: avoid
Item.description: Use as state, if it cannot be avoided (but only if variable appears differentiated and no other potential state with attribute default, prefer, or always can be selected).

Item.name: default
Item.description: Use as state if appropriate, but only if variable appears differentiated.

Item.name: prefer
Item.description: Prefer it as state over those having the default value (also variables can be selected, which do not appear differentiated).

Item.name: always
Item.description: Do use it as a state.

Item.name: Entering
Item.description: Fluid flow is only entering

Item.name: Leaving
Item.description: Fluid flow is only leaving

Item.name: Bidirectional
Item.description: No restrictions on fluid flow (flow reversal possible)

Item.name: stratified
Item.description: Stratified two phase flow (Fjalestad)

Item.name: mixedTwoPhase
Item.description: Mixed, two phase flow (Masoneillan)

Item.name: mixedCompressible
Item.description: Mixed, compressible flow
